.TH LRM 1 "November 2025" "lrm 0.7.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lrm \- Linux-native CLI tool for managing .NET .resx localization files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lrm
[\fIGLOBAL OPTIONS\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR
[\fICOMMAND OPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B LRM
(Localization Resource Manager) is a powerful, Linux-native command-line tool for managing .NET localization files (.resx and JSON formats) with an interactive Terminal UI.
.PP
Features include:
.IP \(bu 2
Interactive Terminal UI for visual editing
.IP \(bu 2
Machine translation support (Google, DeepL, OpenAI, Claude, Ollama)
.IP \(bu 2
CI/CD automation workflows
.IP \(bu 2
Validation and placeholder checking
.IP \(bu 2
Code scanning for unused/missing keys
.IP \(bu 2
Backup system with diff view
.IP \(bu 2
Multi-platform support (Linux x64/ARM64)
.IP \(bu 2
Web UI with REST API for browser-based management
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-path " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to Resources folder (default: current directory)
.TP
.BR \-\-backend " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Resource format backend: json or resx (auto-detected if not specified)
.TP
.BR \-\-config\-file " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to configuration file (optional, default: auto-discover lrm.json)
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help information
.SH COMMANDS
.SS init
Initialize a new localization project.
.PP
.B lrm init
[\fB\-i\fR|\fB\-\-interactive\fR]
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
[\fB\-\-default\-lang\fR \fICODE\fR]
[\fB\-\-languages\fR \fICODES\fR]
[\fB\-\-base\-name\fR \fINAME\fR]
[\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interactive
Run interactive setup wizard
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Resource format: json (default), resx
.TP
.BR \-\-default\-lang " " \fICODE\fR
Default language code (e.g., en, en-US)
.TP
.BR \-\-languages " " \fICODES\fR
Additional language codes, comma-separated (e.g., fr,de,el)
.TP
.BR \-\-base\-name " " \fINAME\fR
Base filename for resources (default: strings)
.SS convert
Convert resource files between formats (RESX and JSON).
.PP
.B lrm convert
[\fB\-\-from\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
[\fB\-\-to\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
[\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-nested\fR]
[\fB\-\-include\-comments\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
[\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-from " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Source format: resx or json (auto-detected if not specified)
.TP
.BR \-\-to " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Target format: resx or json
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIPATH\fR
Output directory (default: same as source)
.TP
.BR \-\-nested
Convert dot-separated keys to nested structure (JSON only)
.TP
.BR \-\-include\-comments
Preserve comments in output (default: true)
.SS validate
Validate resource files for missing translations, duplicates, and errors.
.PP
.B lrm validate
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
[\fB\-\-missing\-only\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: table (default), json, simple
.TP
.BR \-\-missing\-only
Show only missing translations
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-backup
Skip automatic backup before validation
.SS stats
Display translation statistics and coverage.
.PP
.B lrm stats
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: table (default), json, simple
.SS view
View details of a specific key or pattern across all languages.
.PP
.B lrm view
\fIKEY_PATTERN\fR
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
[\fB\-\-cultures\fR \fICULTURES\fR]
[\fB\-\-search\-in\fR \fISCOPE\fR]
[\fB\-\-status\fR \fISTATUS\fR]
[\fB\-\-keys\-only\fR]
[\fB\-\-count\fR]
[\fB\-\-sort\fR]
[\fB\-\-not\fR \fIPATTERN\fR]
.TP
.I KEY_PATTERN
Key name or regex pattern (e.g., "SaveButton", "Error.*", "*.Text")
.TP
.BR \-\-search\-in " " \fISCOPE\fR
Search scope: keys (default), values, comments, both
.TP
.BR \-\-cultures " " \fICULTURES\fR
Comma-separated list of cultures to display
.TP
.BR \-\-status " " \fISTATUS\fR
Filter by translation status: translated, untranslated, all (default)
.SS add
Add a new key to all language files.
.PP
.B lrm add
\fIKEY\fR
[\fB\-i\fR|\fB\-\-interactive\fR]
[\fB\-\-lang\fR \fICULTURE\fR:\fIVALUE\fR]
[\fB\-\-ask\-missing\fR]
[\fB\-\-plural\fR]
[\fB\-\-plural\-form\fR \fIFORM\fR:\fIVALUE\fR]
[\fB\-\-comment\fR \fICOMMENT\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.I KEY
The key name to add
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interactive
Interactive mode (prompts for values in all languages)
.TP
.BR \-\-lang " " \fICULTURE\fR:\fIVALUE\fR
Specify value for a specific language (can be repeated)
.TP
.BR \-\-ask\-missing
Prompt for missing language values. By default, unspecified languages will have empty values.
.TP
.BR \-\-plural
Create a plural key with multiple forms (JSON only). Use with \fB\-i\fR for interactive plural form entry.
.TP
.BR \-\-plural\-form " " \fIFORM\fR:\fIVALUE\fR
Plural form value (can be repeated). Valid forms: zero, one, two, few, many, other. Example: \fB\-\-plural\-form one:"{0} item" \-\-plural\-form other:"{0} items"\fR
.TP
.BR \-\-comment " " \fICOMMENT\fR
Optional comment for the resource entry
.SS update
Update values for an existing key.
.PP
.B lrm update
\fIKEY\fR
[\fB\-\-lang\fR \fICULTURE\fR:\fIVALUE\fR]
[\fB\-\-plural\-form\fR \fIFORM\fR:\fIVALUE\fR]
[\fB\-\-comment\fR \fICOMMENT\fR]
[\fB\-i\fR|\fB\-\-interactive\fR]
[\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-lang " " \fICULTURE\fR:\fIVALUE\fR
Specify value for a specific language (can be repeated)
.TP
.BR \-\-plural\-form " " \fIFORM\fR:\fIVALUE\fR
Update plural form value for existing plural keys (can be repeated). Valid forms: zero, one, two, few, many, other.
.TP
.BR \-\-comment " " \fICOMMENT\fR
Optional comment for the resource entry
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interactive
Interactive mode (prompts for values in all languages)
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Skip confirmation prompts
.SS delete
Delete a key from all language files.
.PP
.B lrm delete
\fIKEY\fR
[\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Skip confirmation prompt
.SS merge\-duplicates
Merge duplicate key occurrences into a single entry.
.PP
.B lrm merge\-duplicates
\fIKEY\fR
[\fB\-\-auto\-merge\fR]
[\fB\-\-keep\fR \fIINDEX\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.SS export
Export translations to CSV, JSON, or text format.
.PP
.B lrm export
[\fB\-o\fR \fIFILE\fR]
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Output file path (default: Resources.csv)
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Export format: csv (default), json, text
.SS import
Import translations from CSV file.
.PP
.B lrm import
\fIFILE\fR
[\fB\-\-validate\-after\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-validate\-after
Run validation after import
.SS edit
Launch interactive Terminal UI editor.
.PP
.B lrm edit
[\fB\-\-source\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-source\-path " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to source code directory for code scanning (default: parent directory of resource path)
