.SS add\-language
Create a new language file.
.PP
.B lrm add\-language
\fB\-\-culture\fR \fICULTURE\fR
[\fB\-\-copy\-from\fR \fISOURCE\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-culture " " \fICULTURE\fR
Culture code (e.g., fr, de, es)
.TP
.BR \-\-copy\-from " " \fISOURCE\fR
Copy values from source culture (default: default)
.SS remove\-language
Delete a language file.
.PP
.B lrm remove\-language
\fB\-\-culture\fR \fICULTURE\fR
[\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.SS list\-languages
List all detected language files.
.PP
.B lrm list\-languages
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
.SS backup list
List all backup versions.
.PP
.B lrm backup list
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
[\fB\-\-limit\fR \fIN\fR]
.SS backup create
Create a manual backup.
.PP
.B lrm backup create
[\fB\-\-description\fR \fIDESC\fR]
.SS backup restore
Restore from a backup version.
.PP
.B lrm backup restore
\fB\-\-version\fR \fIN\fR
[\fB\-\-preview\fR]
[\fB\-\-keys\fR \fIKEYS\fR]
[\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
.SS backup diff
Compare two backup versions or current state.
.PP
.B lrm backup diff
\fB\-\-version\fR \fIN\fR
[\fB\-\-compare\-to\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
.SS backup info
View backup metadata and statistics.
.PP
.B lrm backup info
\fB\-\-version\fR \fIN\fR
.SS backup prune
Clean up old backup versions.
.PP
.B lrm backup prune
[\fB\-\-keep\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB\-\-older\-than\fR \fIDAYS\fR]
[\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR]
.SS scan
Scan source code for localization key usage.
.PP
.B lrm scan
[\fB\-\-source\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-resource\-classes\fR \fICLASSES\fR]
[\fB\-\-localization\-methods\fR \fIMETHODS\fR]
[\fB\-\-strict\fR]
[\fB\-\-show\-unused\fR]
[\fB\-\-show\-missing\fR]
[\fB\-\-exclude\fR \fIPATTERN\fR]
[\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-source\-path " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to source code (default: parent directory)
.TP
.BR \-\-file " " \fIPATH\fR
Scan a single file instead of entire codebase
.TP
.BR \-\-resource\-classes " " \fICLASSES\fR
Comma-separated resource class names
.TP
.BR \-\-strict
High-confidence static references only
.SS translate
Automatically translate keys using machine translation.
.PP
.B lrm translate
[\fB\-\-provider\fR \fIPROVIDER\fR]
[\fB\-\-target\-languages\fR \fILANGS\fR]
[\fB\-\-only\-missing\fR]
[\fB\-\-keys\fR \fIKEYS\fR]
[\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-provider " " \fIPROVIDER\fR
Translation provider: google, deepl, libretranslate, azure, openai, claude, azureopenai, ollama
.TP
.BR \-\-target\-languages " " \fILANGS\fR
Comma-separated target language codes
.TP
.BR \-\-only\-missing
Translate only missing values
.SS config
Manage translation provider configuration.
.PP
.B lrm config
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR
.PP
Subcommands:
.IP \(bu 2
.B list-providers
- List available translation providers
.IP \(bu 2
.B set-api-key
- Set API key for a provider
.IP \(bu 2
.B get-api-key
- Check where an API key is configured
.IP \(bu 2
.B delete-api-key
- Remove an API key from the store
.SS cloud
Cloud synchronization commands for LRM Cloud.
.PP
.B lrm cloud
\fISUBCOMMAND\fR
.PP
Subcommands:
.IP \(bu 2
.B login \fIHOST\fR
- Authenticate with LRM Cloud via browser
.IP \(bu 2
.B logout
- Clear stored authentication tokens
.IP \(bu 2
.B status
- Show cloud sync status
.IP \(bu 2
.B push
- Push local changes to cloud
.IP \(bu 2
.B pull
- Pull remote changes from cloud
.IP \(bu 2
.B set-token
- Manually set an authentication token
.IP \(bu 2
.B set-api-key
- Store a CLI API key for cloud authentication
.IP \(bu 2
.B remote
- Remote URL configuration (set, get, unset)
.SS cloud set\-api\-key
Store a CLI API key for cloud authentication.
.PP
.B lrm cloud set\-api\-key
[\fB\-\-key\fR \fIKEY\fR]
[\fB\-\-host\fR \fIHOST\fR]
[\fB\-\-remove\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-key " " \fIKEY\fR
API key to store (will prompt if not provided)
.TP
.BR \-\-host " " \fIHOST\fR
Remote host (auto-detected from remote URL if configured)
.TP
.BR \-\-remove
Remove stored API key instead of setting one
.PP
API keys provide an alternative to JWT authentication for CI/CD pipelines and automation.
Priority: environment variable (LRM_CLOUD_API_KEY) > stored key > JWT token
.SS chain
Execute multiple LRM commands sequentially in a single invocation.
.PP
.B lrm chain
\fICOMMANDS\fR
[\fB\-\-continue\-on\-error\fR]
[\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
.TP
.I COMMANDS
Commands to execute, separated by ' -- ' (space-dash-dash-space)
.TP
.BR \-\-continue\-on\-error
Continue executing commands even if one fails (default: stop on first error)
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
Show what commands would be executed without running them
.PP
Examples:
.TP
Translation workflow:
.B lrm chain validate --format json -- translate --only-missing -- export -o output.csv
.TP
Validation and scanning:
.B lrm chain validate -- scan --strict
.TP
Backup before update:
.B lrm chain backup create -- update SaveButton --lang default:"Save" -- validate
.TP
Dry run to preview:
.B lrm chain validate -- translate --only-missing --dry-run
.SS web
Start web server with REST API and Blazor UI for browser-based management.
.PP
.B lrm web
[\fB\-\-port\fR \fIPORT\fR]
[\fB\-\-bind\-address\fR \fIADDRESS\fR]
[\fB\-\-source\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-open\-browser\fR]
[\fB\-\-enable\-https\fR]
[\fB\-\-cert\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-cert\-password\fR \fIPASSWORD\fR]
.TP
.BR \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fR
Port to bind the web server to (default: 5000)
.TP
.BR \-\-bind\-address " " \fIADDRESS\fR
Address to bind to: localhost, 0.0.0.0, * (default: localhost)
.TP
.BR \-\-source\-path " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to source code directory for code scanning
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-open\-browser
Do not automatically open browser on startup
.TP
.BR \-\-enable\-https
Enable HTTPS
.TP
.BR \-\-cert\-path " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to HTTPS certificate file (.pfx)
.TP
.BR \-\-cert\-password " " \fIPASSWORD\fR
Password for HTTPS certificate
.PP
The web server provides:
.IP \(bu 2
REST API at /api/* endpoints
.IP \(bu 2
Swagger UI at /swagger
.IP \(bu 2
Blazor Server UI at root URL
.IP \(bu 2
All CLI features accessible via browser
