.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Initialize a new JSON localization project:
.B lrm init \-\-format json \-\-default\-lang en \-\-languages fr,de,el
.TP
Initialize with interactive wizard:
.B lrm init \-i
.TP
Convert RESX files to JSON format:
.B lrm convert \-\-to json
.TP
Convert JSON to RESX with nested keys flattened:
.B lrm convert \-\-from json \-\-to resx
.TP
Validate all resource files:
.B lrm validate
.TP
View translation statistics:
.B lrm stats
.TP
Launch interactive editor:
.B lrm edit
.TP
View a specific key:
.B lrm view SaveButton
.TP
View keys matching a pattern:
.B lrm view "Error.*"
.TP
Add a new key interactively:
.B lrm add NewKey \-i
.TP
Translate missing values with Google:
.B lrm translate \-\-only\-missing \-\-provider google \-\-target\-languages fr,de,es
.TP
Export to CSV:
.B lrm export \-o translations.csv
.TP
Scan source code for unused keys:
.B lrm scan \-\-show\-unused
.TP
Create a backup:
.B lrm backup create \-\-description "Before major refactoring"
.TP
List backups:
.B lrm backup list
.TP
Restore from backup:
.B lrm backup restore \-\-version 5 \-\-preview
.TP
Start web server:
.B lrm web
.TP
Start web server on custom port:
.B lrm web \-\-port 8080 \-\-bind\-address 0.0.0.0
